Now I have a good understanding. Looking at the rwsdk README, the worker entry point uses `defineApp` from `rwsdk/worker` and `route` from `rwsdk/router`. The route handlers receive `RequestInfo` which doesn't include `env`.

However, looking at the global `Env` type declaration in `worker.d.ts`:
```typescript
declare global {
    type Env = {
        ASSETS: Fetcher;
        DB: D1Database;
